TEXT(beginproblem());

##############################################################
#
#  Setup
#
#


Context("Numeric");
#given
$A = random(1, 3, 1);
$B = random(4, 6, 1);
$C = random(5, 10, 1);

#computation
$theta = asin(($A)/$B);
$angle = $theta*180/pi;
$vm = $B*cos($theta);
$t = $C/$vm;

$width = 350;
$height = 300;
#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.03,
tolType=>'relative');

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

Olympians are finding new creative ways to train. One swimmer uses their local river, one that moves with a velocity of [`[$A]`] [`m/s`] downstream in the direction indicated. The olympians speed is averaged at [`[$B]`] [`m/s`]. What angle must the swimmer leave at in order to get directly across the river?

[@ image( "20-P-KM-AF-029.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

[`\theta = `][_____]{"$angle"}[`^\circ`]


What is the time to cross if [` r = [$C] `] [`m`]?

[`t = `][_____]{"$t"}[`s`]

END_PGML

